{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP is the core risk: extraction completeness over varied legal phrasing depends on real model behavior and can vary across runs/prompts. A mocked extractor would hide real misses (MOCK-HIDE). No multi-agent sequence is required for this behavior alone, so Workflow is higher than needed.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a curated set of real contracts with gold annotations for parties/dates/obligations/penalties, and fail if required key terms are missed beyond threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk assessor flags language that would be problematic under the configured risk policy, even when the problematic phrasing is indirect or euphemistic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is model quality on nuanced semantic interpretation (indirect/euphemistic phrasing), which is inherently LLM-dependent. Mocked responses would not expose true false negatives on subtle language (MOCK-HIDE). Single reviewer behavior, so not Workflow-minimum.","test_description":"Evaluate the real risk-assessor model against a policy-labeled corpus containing direct and euphemistic risky clauses; assert recall/precision targets for policy-defined risk categories.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.9,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The compliance checker correctly determines whether the contract meets all applicable regulatory requirements for the configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on model judgment over legal/regulatory text and jurisdiction context (LLM-DEP). Deterministic unit tests can verify rule plumbing, but they cannot catch model misclassification on real contracts. This behavior is not inherently multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Run the real compliance-checker model on jurisdiction-specific benchmark contracts with known compliance outcomes; verify decision accuracy and required citation/requirement mapping per jurisdiction config.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments (e.g., extractor says 'standard' but risk assessor says 'high risk'), the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure boundary is module handoff/schema reconciliation between reviewer outputs and merge logic (MOCK-MISS). This can be tested with deterministic fixture outputs from two reviewer modules and real merge wiring. No real LLM call is required to catch preservation/attribution bugs for this behavior.","test_description":"Feed realistic reviewer-output payloads (including conflicting assessments on same clause IDs/spans) through the real merge module and assert unified report retains both assessments with correct reviewer attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — dispatching to all three reviewers, collecting results, merging into a unified report — completes correctly for a real contract without losing any individual reviewer's findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior spans multiple agentic steps (three real AI reviewers) plus orchestration and merge (MULTI-STEP + LLM-DEP). End-to-end failures include async fan-out/fan-in, partial result loss, and cross-step data integrity that lower-level tests can miss. Real pipeline execution is needed.","test_description":"Execute the end-to-end pipeline on real contracts using all three live reviewers in parallel, then verify final report includes each reviewer’s findings and conflict records without drops across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.75}}]}
